{"add":{"doc":{"id":"103a19a349d5933ba1d398406c5ba35636e7e1f8021740dd074b446ff6517c5a","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0b/Shefa_Tal.png/135px-Shefa_Tal.png","previous":[],"after":["Divine creation by means of the Ten Sefirot is an ethical process. They represent the different aspects of Morality. Loving-Kindness is a possible moral justification found in Chessed, and Gevurah is the Moral Justification of Justice and both are mediated by Mercy which is Rachamim. However, these pillars of morality become immoral once they become extremes. When Loving-Kindness become extreme it can lead to sexual depravity and lack of Justice to the wicked. When Justice becomes extreme, it can lead to torture and the Murder of innocents and unfair punishment."]}}}